  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skin on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail, peel your <strong>parsnip[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then into batons</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>into discs</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>red</strong> <strong>onion[s] </strong>in half, then cut <strong>half</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1710861843281-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1710861843281-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1710861843281-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1710861843281-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1710861843281-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped vegetables</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a small pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 20-25 min or until golden and tender</p><p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>carrot</strong></p><p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710861848227-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710861848227-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710861848227-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710861848227-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710861848227-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>diced carrot </strong>to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1710861851267-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1710861851267-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1710861851267-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1710861851267-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1710861851267-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and carrot is starting to soften, turn the heat up to high, then add your<strong> lean beef mince</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Once browned, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>mango chutney </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1-2 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1710861856346-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1710861856346-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1710861856346-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1710861856346-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1710861856346-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)<strong> </strong>and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and reduce the heat to medium-high, then cook for 3-4 min further or until the sauce has thickened, then season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and transfer to an <strong>oven-proof</strong> <strong>dish</strong> (use individual ones for fancy presentation!) – this is your<strong> pie mix</strong></p><p>Dust your work surface generously with <strong>flour</strong>,<strong> </strong>unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong>, roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a<strong> rolling pin </strong>and cut to the size of your pie dish[es]</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1710861860068-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1710861860068-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1710861860068-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1710861860068-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1710861860068-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Lay the <strong>puff pastry</strong> over the dish[es], trim off any excess (use for fancy pie decorations!) and press the edges with a fork to seal the pastry to the dish[es]</p><p>Brush with a little <strong>water</strong>, add a few <strong>black mustard seeds</strong> to the top (you’ll use the rest later!), then put in the oven for 15-20 min or until puffed up, golden and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>spiced lean</strong> <strong>beef & mango chutney pie</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1710861863567-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1710861863567-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1710861863567-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1710861863567-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1710861863567-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After the veg has had an initial 20-25 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven, add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and the <strong>remaining black mustard seeds</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 5 min – this is your <strong>mustard seed veg</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1710861866713-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1710861866713-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1710861866713-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1710861866713-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1710861866713-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> spiced</strong> <strong>lean beef & mango chutney pie</strong> with the <strong>mustard seed veg </strong>to the side</p><p>Top the veg with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
